Quote:  But a short time ago, a serious altercation arose between the Natives of Orangituapeka and Waimate, three days to the southward of this place: the inhabitants of the former Pa declaring, that they had adopted the bishop's <i>tikanga,</i> and refusing to allow their Missionary, the Rev. J. Skevington (who resides within two miles of the place) to visit them; at the same time using very contemptuous language towards the Natives of Waimate.
